}}{{TIDTOC|adapter}} ==Overview== This unit has a green translucent casing.
"UH400 REV:A20" is silkscreened on the board. :The USB connectors on the device populating this entry (S/N: UH94002623) are from '''FOXLINK''' (the single B) and '''CFK''' (the 4 As). The device is also using a '''Micrel''' MIC 29302BT voltage regulator and two '''Texas Instruments''' TSP2042 USB power distribution switches. All capacitors on the board are branded '''K.K.'''.
The case is also marked with a recycling number. It is number 7 (other), but it is noted as being polycarbonate.
The power adapter that originally came with the device may be an ''unbranded'' MKD-48062100 (120VAC ~ 60Hz, 25W -> 6VDC 2.1A).
